'''''Euphorbia boissieri''''' is a species of [[plant]] in the [[Euphorbiaceae]] family. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Madagascar]].  Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]]. A political crisis in 2009 also plunged Madagascar wildlife into a desperate state. [http://www.wildmadagascar.org]  It is named after botanist [[Pierre Edmond Boissier]].

