==Governmental flags ==
{| class="wikitable" |- ! style="width:110px;"|Flag!!style="width:100px;"|Date!!style="width:250px;"|Use!!style="width:250px;"|Description |- | [[File:Flag of the President of Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 1988—Present || Presidential standard || Blue, with the arms of Malta in the centre and a golden Maltese cross in each corner. Ratio: 2:3. |- | || 1814—Present || Commissioner of the Police Force|| Blue triangular pennant with a silver representation of the Malta Police badge in the centre. |- | [[File:Flag of the Archbishop of Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 754—Present || Archbishop's standard || A papal flag (two equal vertical stripes, yellow and white), but with the ratio: 2:3. |}
==Military flags ==
{| class="wikitable" |- ! style="width:110px;"|Flag!!style="width:100px;"|Date!!style="width:250px;"|Use!!style="width:250px;"|Description |- | [[File:Flag of Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 1964—Present || Military ensign|| Identical to the State flag. White and red, augmented in the canton by a depiction of the British [[George Cross]]. Ratio 2:3. |- | [[File:Naval Jack of Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 1964—Present || Naval jack|| A George Cross proper fimbriated in red in the centre of a white square, within a red square. Each corner of the red square shall contain a white Maltese Cross. Ratio: 1:1. |- | || c.1973—Present || Commander of the Armed Forces' Pennant|| A red triangular pennant with golden emblem of the Armed Forces. The emblem is a mason tower of de Redin, which represents fortification and Malta defences back to the time of the knights of St. John. |}
==Historical flags== {| class="wikitable" |- ! style="width:110px;"|Flag!!style="width:100px;"|Date!!style="width:250px;"|Use!!style="width:250px;"|Description |- | [[File:Flag of the Sovereign Military Order of Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 1530–1798 ||Flag of the [[Knights Hospitaller|Order of Saint John]] used in Malta|| Red rectangular flag quartered by a white cross. |- | [[File:Flag of France.svg|border|100px]] || 1798–1800 ||[[Flag of France]] used in Malta|| A vertical [[tricolour (flag)|tricolour]] of blue, white, and red. |- | [[File:Flag of the Kingdom of the Two Sicilies (1816).svg|border|100px]] || 1798–1813 ||[[Flag of Sicily]] used in Malta|| A white flag with the coat of arms of Sicily |- | [[File:Union flag 1606 (Kings Colors).svg|border|100px]] || 1798–1801 ||[[Union Jack#History|Flag of Great Britain]] used in Malta|| A superimposition of the flags of [[England]] and [[Scotland]]. |- | [[File:Flag of the United Kingdom.svg|border|100px]] || 1801 onwards ||[[Union Jack|Flag of Great Britain and Ireland]] used in Malta|| A superimposition of the flags of [[England]] and [[Scotland]] with the [[Saint Patrick's Flag|Saint Patrick's Saltire]] (representing [[Ireland]]). |- | [[File:19th Century Flag of Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 19th century ||British Malta State ensign|| Red Ensign with a white St George's cross, but no badge. |- | [[File:Flag of Malta (1875–1898).svg|border|100px]] || 1875–c.1898 ||British Malta State ensign|| Blue ensign. Badge: A white Maltese cross on white and red panel framed with ''ginger-bread''. |- | [[File:Flag of Malta (1898-1923).svg|border|100px]] || c.1898–1923 ||British Malta State ensgin || Blue ensign. Badge: On a white circle a white and red shield with pointed top and gold border. |- | [[File:Flag of Malta (1923-1943).svg|border|100px]] || 1923–1943 ||British Malta State ensign || Blue ensign. Badge: White and red shield with pointed top and gold border. |- | [[File:Flag of Malta (1943-1964).svg|border|100px]] || 1943–1964 ||[[British Malta]] State ensign || Blue ensign. Badge: On a white circle a white and red flat top shield with George Cross on blue canton. |- | [[File:Unofficial Flag of Malta (pre-1943).svg|border|100px]] || Before 1943 ||Malta Civil Flag (Unofficial)|| Undefaced white-red vertical bicolor. Ratio 2:3. |- | [[File:Flag of Malta (1943).svg|border|100px]] || 1943–1964 ||Malta Civil Flag (Unofficial)|| White-red vertical bicolor with George Cross on blue canton. |- | [[File:Royal Standard of Malta (1964–1974).svg|border|100px]] || 1967–1974 ||Queen Elizabeth II's Personal Flag for Malta || One of [[Flags of Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II's personal flags]]. This flag was used to represent her as Queen of Malta until it was made redundant by the introduction of a republican form of government in 1974.
It featured the [[coat of arms of Malta|arms of Malta]] in [[banner of arms|banner form]] defaced with the device from [[Personal Flag of Queen Elizabeth II|her Personal Flag]]: a blue roundel with a crowned "E" surrounded by a wreath of gold roses.<ref>[http://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/mt%5Eqeii.html "Queen Elizabeth II's Personal Flag for Malta 1967-1974 (Malta)"], ''Flags of the World'' website. Retrieved 21 November 2012.</ref> Ratio 2:3. |- | [[File:Flag of the Governor of Malta (1875–1898).svg|border|100px]] || 1875-c. 1898 ||Governor's Flag|| Badge: A white Maltese cross on white and red panel framed with ''ginger-bread'', on a white circle surrounded by a garland on the Union Flag. |- | [[File:Flag of the Governor of Malta (1898–1943).svg|border|100px]] || c.1898–1943 ||Governor's Flag || Badge: White and red shield with pointed top and gold border, on a white circle surrounded by a garland on the Union Flag. |- | [[File:Flag of the Governor of Malta (1943–1964).svg|border|100px]] || 1943–1964 ||Governor's Flag || On a white circle surrounded by a garland on the Union Flag of the Governor. |- | [[File:Flag of the Governor-General of Malta (1964–1974).svg|border|100px]] || 1964–1974 ||Governor-General's Flag ||Commonwealth blue with the Royal Crest and Malta scroll. |}
==Local Councils== Some flags had been used prior to the creation of local councils in 1993. The coats of arms of the local councils are officially recognised, however the flags are not and thus a number of variants exist. Since 1993, a new local council, [[Mtarfa]], has been created, and the local councils of [[Attard]], [[Birżebbuġa]], [[Floriana]], [[Kalkara]], [[Lija]], [[Mellieħa]], [[Mġarr]], [[Mosta]], [[Nadur]], [[Naxxar]], [[Paola, Malta|Paola]], [[Qrendi]], [[Siġġiewi]], [[Xgħajra]] and [[Żebbuġ, Malta|Żebbuġ]] have changed their flags and coats of arms. Some, such as Mosta, had minor differences, but others, like Xgħajra changed the arms completely.
===Malta=== {| class="wikitable" |- ! style="width:110px;"|Flag!!style="width:100px;"|Date!!style="width:250px;"|Use!!style="width:250px;"|Description |- | [[File:Flag of Attard.svg|border|100px]] || 2000—Present || [[Attard]] (village) || A blue cross that represents [[Roman Catholicism]] and [[St. Mary]] with a red square in the middle on white background. Current flag adopted in 2000, previous flag was similar but with white central square. |- | [[File:Balzan.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Balzan]] (village) || A red horizontal line between two some horizontal green lines, on white background. |- | [[File:Flag of Birgu.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Birgu|Birgu - Città Vittoriosa]] (city) || Sword held upright and laurel are symbolizing the winner, olive probably the peace afterwards. A number of variants of the flag are known to exist. |- | [[File:BirkirkaraHTML.gif|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Birkirkara]] (town) || Horizontally divided red over white, the top (red) stripe about half as wide as the bottom (white) one. A royal crown centred on the red stripe, a red Greek cross centred on the white stripe. |- ||| 2000—Present || [[Birżebbuġa]] (village) || An [[olive]] plant representing this locality, and the colour blue because it is near the sea. Current flag adopted in 2000, previous flag was dark blue with a yellow chain in orle and two yellow crossed keys in the centre. |- | [[File:BormlaHTML.gif|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Bormla|Bormla - Città Cospicua]] (city) || A [[cotton]] plant on a yellow background. |- | [[File:Flag of Dingli.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Dingli]] (village) || Segmented diagonally in four triangles: two light blue facing each other horizontally and two red ones facing each other vertically, all separated with a white band. |- | [[File:Flag of Il-Fgura.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Fgura]] (town) || A white flag with a red horizontal line, and three gold stars on the line. Similar to the flag of [[Kerċem]]. |- | [[File:Flag of Floriana, Malta.png|border|100px]] || 2006—Present || [[Floriana|Furjana]] (town) || Red rampant lion on a white background, taken from the coat of arms of Grandmaster [[António Manoel de Vilhena]]. Current flag adopted in 2006, previous flag was divided per pale. The dexter side showed a red rampant lion with a golden head in a white field. The sinister side showed a golden winged arm holding upright a sword in natural colour. It was based on the coat of arms of the same Grandmaster. A variant of this flag also existed. |- | [[File:Flag of Gudja.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Gudja]] (village) || White flag with a red pointed bar. |- | [[File:MLT Gżira flag.gif|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Gżira]] (town) || A blue flag with a white wavy stripe from the top hoist to the bottom fly; on the top fly, a yellow heraldic ship, on the bottom hoist a yellow heraldic dolphin with a red tongue. |- | [[File:GharghulSVG.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Għargħur]] (village) || A white flag with a red triangle from the bottom and a red star on top. |- | [[File:Flag of Ghaxaq.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Għaxaq]] (village) || White flag defaced by three green bars. |- | [[File:Hamrun.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Ħamrun]] (town) || Red flag with a white border. A variant flag is known to exist. |- | [[File:Flag of Iklin.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Iklin]] (village) || Blue flag with Saint Michael holding a flaming sword and a shield with a green cross. Similar to the [[Flag of Kiev]]. |- | [[File:Flag of Isla.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Senglea|Isla - Città Invicta]] (city) || A yellow flag with a black saltire, on its ends and centre five white pilgrim's scallops. |- | || 2009—Present || [[Kalkara]] (village) || Yellow and blue flag with a flame erupting from the line joining the two fields, with a green border. Current flag adopted in 2009, previous flag with flame on blue field and no green border. |- | [[File:Flag of Kirkop.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Kirkop]] (village) || White flag with a red band in the centre, connected to the bottom with another red band forming a shape similar to that of a T. |- | [[File:MLT Lija flag.gif|border|100px]] || 2000—Present || [[Lija]] (village) || Orange branch with three oranges, with a red square on the left and a red one on the right. Current flag adopted in 2000, previous flag had an orange tree. |- | [[File:Luqa.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Luqa]] (village) || White flag with a red saltire. Similar to the [[Saint Patrick's Saltire]] and the flag of [[Marsaxlokk]]. |- | [[File:Flag of Marsa.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Marsa, Malta|Marsa]] (town) || A sailing ship on a red and white or blue and white background. |- | [[File:Flag of Marsaskala.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Marsaskala]] (village) || Green flag divided by a downward pointing wedge shaped like an equilateral or at least nearly equilateral triangle. The wedge is white with three blue wavy fessy lines. |- | [[File:Flag of Marsaxlokk.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Marsaxlokk]] (village) || White flag with a blue saltire. A variant flag is known to exist. Similar the flag of [[Luqa]]. |- | [[File:MelliehaHTML.svg|border|100px]] || 2000—Present || [[Mellieħa]] (village) || Blue flag with a white six-pointed star and a golden chevron. Current flag adopted in 2000, previous flag was a blue field with a sinister bendy white line and a white 5-point star upon the sinister chief point. |- | [[File:Flag of Mdina municipality, Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Mdina]] (city) || Undefaced white-red vertical bicolor. This was the unofficial flag of Malta until 1943. A variant flag is known to exist. |- | [[File:MLT Mġarr flag.gif|border|100px]] || 2000—Present || [[Mgarr|Mġarr]] (village) || A trilithon, symbol of [[Skorba]] Temples, on wavy blue and white lines. Current flag adopted in 2000, previous flag was blue with a yellow cartwheel. |- | [[File:Flag of Mosta.svg|border|100px]] || c.2007—Present || [[Mosta]] (town) || A white flag representing the actual town of [[Mosta]] with a red cross representing the [[Roman Catholicism|catholic faith]] among the people of [[Mosta]]. The yellow circle in the middle represents the [[Rotunda of Mosta|Rotunda]], which is one of the most recognised landmarks in [[Malta]], within the circle is a white star on a blue background representing [[Mary (mother of Jesus)|St.Mary]], who is the patron saint of [[Mosta]]. Current flag adopted 2006 or 2007, previous flag had a blue star on a gold circle in the centre. |- | [[File:Mqabba.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Mqabba]] (village) || Red flag with a white stripe from upper hoist to lower fly. |- | [[File:Msida.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Msida]] (town) || Green flag with two white stripes from upper hoist to lower fly. |- | [[File:Flag of Mtarfa.svg|border|100px]] || 2000—Present || [[Mtarfa]] (village) || Flag possibly representing the Mtarfa barracks. |- | [[File:Naxxar.svg|border|100px]] || c.2000—Present || [[Naxxar]] (town) || White-red vertical bicolour, with a counterchanged cross in the middle. Similar to the flags of [[Sliema]] and [[Żurrieq]]. Current flag adopted c.2000, previous flag was similar but cross horizontally counterchanged. |- | || c.2000—Present || [[Paola, Malta|Paola]] (village) || Three spirals on the top part representing the [[Hal Saflieni Hypogeum]]. The three peacocks in the lower part are derived from the arms of the original founder of the town Grand Master [[Antoine de Paule]]. Current flag adopted c.2000, previous flag was a golden spiral on a red background. |- | [[File:Flag of Pembroke.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Pembroke, Malta|Pembroke]] (village) || Fourteen castles representing the coastal watchtowers erected by Grand Master Martin De Redin. The swords represent the fact that Pembroke was built on former British barracks. |- | [[File:PietaHTML.gif|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Pietà, Malta|Pietà]] (village) || A pelican sitting in a nest with several ducklings, feeding them by letting some blood from her chest, thus vulning herself. |- | [[File:Flag of Qormi.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Qormi|Qormi - Città Pinto]] (city) || ''A white flag with the five crescents of [[Manuel Pinto de Fonseca]]. |- | [[File:Flag of Qrendi.svg|border|100px]] || 2000—Present || [[Qrendi]] (village) || White star on a blue flag with a yellow border. Current flag adopted in 2000, previous flag had no border. |- | [[File:Rabat Malta flag.png|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Rabat, Malta|Rabat]] (town) || Flag of [[Mdina]] defaced by an olive branch. |- | [[File:Flag of Safi.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Safi, Malta|Safi]] (village) || White flag defaced by a single blue bar. |- | [[File:Flag of San Ġiljan.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[St. Julian's|San Ġiljan - Portus Sancti Juliani]] (village) || White flag with three vertical red bars. |- | [[File:MLT San Ġwann flag.gif|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[San Ġwann]] (town) || The paschal lamb, a usual attribute of St John the Baptist on a red background. |- | [[File:Flag of Saint Paul's Bay.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[St Paul's Bay|San Pawl il-Baħar]] (town) || The wavy lines are symbolizing the bay. Snake and sword are the attributes of St. Paul, who is said to be shipwrecked on a small island in the bay. The sword is cross-shaped and therefore represents the new religion. The snake refers to the story told in Acts 28, v. 3-6, where St. Paul is attacked by a snake but isn't injured. He throws the snake into the fire and the locals from that moment believe that he is a God. |- | [[File:Flag of Santa Lucija.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Santa Luċija]] (village) || Sun on a black background. |- | [[File:Flag of Santa Venera.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Santa Venera]] (village) || Red flag with a white bar, and three red [[fleur de lys]] on the bar. The fleur de lys come from the arms of Grandmaster [[Alof de Wignacourt]]. |- | [[File:Flag of Siġġiewi.svg|border|100px]] || 2001—Present || [[Siġġiewi|Siġġiewi - Città Ferdinand]] (city) || A white background with 2 red stripes and a golden cross depicting the villagers' faith in Christianity. A flag half yellow and half red represents this village. Current flag adopted in April 2001, previous flag was similar but with a single red bar in the middle and the cross on the bar.<ref>{{cite web|title=Coat of Arms|url=http://www.siggiewi.gov.mt/default.asp?module=content&id=4|website=Siġġiewi Local Council|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110929134446/http://www.siggiewi.gov.mt/default.asp?module=content&id=4|archivedate=29 September 2011}}</ref> |- | [[File:Flag of Sliema.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Sliema]] (town) || Traditional flag of Malta with a counterchanged Stella Maris. Similar to the flag of [[Naxxar]]. |- | [[File:Flag of Swieqi.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Swieqi]] (village) || Saltire representing the suburb of Saint Andrew's, top and bottom quarters represent the suburb of Ibraġ, and others represent the main village of Swieqi. |- | [[File:Tarxien.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Tarxien]] (village) || White flag divided by two blue vertical stripes. |- | [[File:MLT Ta' Xbiex flag.gif|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Ta' Xbiex]] (village) || A ship's wheel on a green background. |- | [[File:Flag of Valletta, Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || '''[[Valletta|Il-Belt Valletta - Città Umilissima]]''' (capital city) || A red flag with a yellow lion rampant, taken from the arms of Grandmaster de Vallette. |- | [[File:Flag of Xghajra.svg|border|100px]] || 2000—Present || [[Xgħajra]] (village) || The flag represents the beginning of the town, because the town started after the British government built a battery in what is now Xgħajra. The people working there started living round this battery and thus a small hamlet was formed, which eventually evolved into a small town. A variant flag is known to exist. Current flag adopted in 2000, previous flag showed three ears of wheat on a blue background. |- | [[File:Zabbar.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Żabbar|Żabbar - Città Hompesch]] (city) || Red flag with a white saltire. |- | [[File:Flag of Zebbug, Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 2000—Present || [[Żebbuġ, Malta Island|Żebbuġ - Città Rohan]] (city) || A canting olive branch above the arms of Grand Master de Rohan. A variant flag is known to exist. Current flag adopted in 2000, previous flag was similar but without olive branch. |- | [[File:Zejtun flag.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Żejtun|Żejtun - Città Beland]] (city) || White rectangular flag quartered by a green cross. |- | [[File:Zurrieq.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Żurrieq]] (village) || White-blue horizontal bicolour, with a counterchanged cross in the middle. Similar to the flag of [[Naxxar]]. |}
