 || The flag shows St. Lawrence's grill and the palms of martyrdom. |- | [[File:Flag of Sannat.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Sannat]] (village) || A standing bale of wheat with two sickles above it. |- | [[File:Flag of Victoria, Gozo.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || '''[[Victoria, Gozo|Ir-Rabat - Città Victoria]]''' (capital) || The coat of arms of Victoria on a white flag with a red border. Three mountains above the sea in natural colour. The chief with "VR" are the abbreviation of "Victoria Regina" and were added upon [[Queen Victoria]]'s jubilee in 1897. A variant flag is known to exist. |- | [[File:Flag of Xaghra.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Xagħra]] (village) || Motif representing the [[Ggantija]] Temples. |- | [[File:Flag of Xewkija, Malta.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Xewkija]] (village) || Yellow flag with a red bar, and thorns on the yellow parts of the flag. |- | [[File:Flag of Żebbuġ, Gozo.svg|border|100px]] || 1993—Present || [[Żebbuġ, Gozo|Żebbuġ]] (town) || An olive tree, as the growing of olives is of great economic importance to the village, and a chief with three six-pointed stars. |}
