y institutions to become the Marmara University. See:{{cite web|url=http://www.marmara.edu.tr/en/information/history |title=History of Marmara University |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120805114020/http://www.marmara.edu.tr/en/information/history |archivedate=2012-08-05 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> |- |[[Mimar Sinan University of Fine Arts]] |align="center"|1882<ref>Mimar Sinan University of Fine Arts institution was founded on January 1, 1882 as the "School of Fine Arts". Finally renamed as Mimar Sinan University on June 20, 1982. See:[http://www.msgsu.edu.tr/msu/pages/450.aspx History of Mimar Sinan University of Fine Arts] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101029215152/http://www.msgsu.edu.tr/msu/pages/450.aspx |date=2010-10-29 }}</ref> |- |[[Yıldız Technical University]] |align="center"|1911<ref>The history of Yıldız Technical University dates back to [[Kondüktör Mekteb-i Âlisi]] (The Conductors School of Higher Education) founded in 1911. Yıldız University was founded by merging several independent faculties with decree law no.41 dated 20 June 1982. See:[http://www.yildiz.edu.tr/en/history.php History of Yıldız Technical University] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100818043559/http://www.yildiz.edu.tr/en/history.php |date=2010-08-18 }}</ref> |}
