{{Infobox settlement | name = Rocky Island | official_name = Shí Dǎo Island 石岛虚拟镇 | native_name = Shí Dǎo 石岛 | settlement_type = Town | image_skyline = | image_caption = | image_flag = | image_shield = | image_map = File:Aerial view of Woody Island.jpg | map_caption = Rocky Island (left) connected to Woody Island (right) ''circa'' 2010. | coordinates = {{coord|16|50|40|N|112|20|50|E|region:MY|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = South China Sea | pushpin_label = Rocky Island | length_km = 0.4 <!--approximate--> | width_km = 0.22 <!--approximate--> | area_total_km2 = | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = [[China]] | subdivision_type1 = Province | subdivision_name1 = [[Hainan]] | subdivision_type2 = City | subdivision_name2 = [[Sansha]] | government_type = Town | governing_body = Yongxingdao Neighborhood Committee | leader_party = Communist Party | population_as_of = | population_total = | demographics_type1 = Ethnicity | demographics1_title1 = Chinese | demographics1_info1 = 100% | demographics_type2 = Languages | demographics2_title1 = Chinese | demographics2_info1 = 100% | timezone1 = China | utc_offset1 = +8 | timezone1_DST = | postal_code_type = Post code | postal_code = 572000 | area_code_type = Dialing code | area_code = +86 0898 }} '''Rocky Island''' ({{zh|s=石岛|t=石島|p=Shí Dǎo|l=stone island}}; Vietnamese: ''Đảo Đá'') is one of the [[Paracel Islands]] in the [[South China Sea]]. It is under the administration of the [[People's Republic of China]] and guarded by the [[PLA Navy]]. The island is also claimed by [[Taiwan]] and [[Vietnam]].
==Geography== Until 2016-2017, Rocky Island was connected to [[Woody Island, South China Sea|Woody Island]] by an 800 metre concrete causeway. Land reclamation in 2016-2017 has joined the two islands by a larger area of land.<ref>{{cite news|title=Recent developments surrounding the South China Sea|url=http://www.startribune.com/recent-developments-surrounding-the-south-china-sea/413544433/|accessdate=31 March 2017|work=Star Tribune}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=As US-China tussle, Asean frets|url=http://www.atimes.com/article/us-china-tussle-asean-frets-south-china-sea/|accessdate=31 March 2017}}</ref><ref>[https://amti.csis.org/woody-island/ Woody Island], Asia Maritime Transparency Initiative, Center for Strategic & International Studies</ref>
==History== A signals intelligence station was built on Rocky Island in 1995, mainly because the island is the highest point in the Paracel Islands.<ref>{{cite paper |url= http://www.freeman.org/m_online/bodansky/beijing.htm |title= Beijing's surge for the Strait of Malacca |author=Yossef Bodansky}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= Australian expert's opinions on Chinese deployment of air defences on Spratly Islands - News VietNamNet |url=http://english.vietnamnet.vn/fms/marine-sovereignty/151428/australian-expert-s-opinions-on-chinese-deployment-of-air-defences-on-spratly-islands.html |website=english.vietnamnet.vn |accessdate=31 March 2017}}</ref>
