{{Infobox mountain | name = The Lion | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 988 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 650 | prominence_ref = | location = [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]] | range = [[Frankland Range]] | coordinates = {{coord|42|56|52|S|146|03|11|E|type:mountain_region:AU-TAS}} | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''The Lion''' is a [[mountain]] in [[South West Wilderness|South West]] [[Tasmania]]. It lies on the North West end of the [[Frankland Range]] jutting out toward the East from the range toward the [[Reservoir|impoundment]] [[Lake Pedder]]. It is directly South of [[The Cupola, Tasmania|The Cupola]] and North of [[The Citadel, Tasmania|The Citadel]].
